<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9692964124979></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9692964124979><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9692964124979>RE: instill doubt</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9692964124979#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=666><span id=Scholar>Zyphyr</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>91 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 1:00 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>During downtime taget something (anything) and use the skill. Do this whenever you can. If you are in a fight in a place where a running mob isn't going to get you killed, use it (ask your group if they have a problem with this before you do). <br><br>For the downtime practice anything targetable works - NPCs (make sure they aren't close to you if you don't want to agro them), PCs, pets, corpses, boats...<br>&nbsp;<br>Zyphyr Runnersbane<br>60th Vending Machine<br>Cult of the Ancient Wyrm<br>Solusek Ro<br></td></tr>
