	   <tr><td colspan=2> Thank you for posting that. I think it's very informative. I have seen the skill rise much quicker after about 40-45, that's for sure. Now I'm at about 55 and it still seems to be taking forever.<br> One thing I'm not sure about is the following sentence: "The skill will only rise on a successful skill check." <br> What is a successful skill check? It can't mean *to my understanding* that you actually had to fear someone, or else it wouldn't work with boats, corpses, npc, etc. I know I've had it increase even when I wasn't successful, while fighting for instance, so I'm a bit unclear.<br> Anyway, the only other thing I wanted to comment on is under the heading of 'Timing ID and your specials'. <br> Because I solo often, I usually need my special attack *Tiger Claw* and doing it the way described above just doesn't allow you to use your special skill enough times in a fight. Here's what I do:<br> Because Tiger Claw cycles through quicker than ID, I hit Instill Doubt first. Right afterward *almost instantaneously* I hit Tiger Claw. By the time ID has 'kicked', Tiger Claw is already back, and I hit it again right after the 'kick'. By the time ID has refreshed *maybe a second or two after your second Tiger Claw*, you're ready to start the process over again. This way you get two special attacks while still practicing your ID. I hope this makes sense. It's pretty late and I've had a rough day, but I hope this might help some of you out :) Take care you Monks of Norrath, you Protectors of Antonica *and Kunark*.<br>&nbsp;<br>Beleni<br>Lowly Monk on Karana</td></tr>
