	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>EK is a very good place to hunt for both melee and casters.&nbsp;&nbsp;Be careful with the spiders, they are social.  Gorge Hounds will agro easily if you're to close, nasty if it happens in the middle of a fight.  Watch out for the Cyclops.  There are three incarnations of that rare spawn.  Higher Levels like to try him, but then find out he's too much and train him to the Wooden Bridge.  The wooden bridge is excellent for casters in thier mid-high teens.   Lots of room for kiters to work (If they're carful).  Wizards are fun to root and nuke.  Decent variety of different Level Creatures.   Snakes, gorge Hounds, Carrion Spiders being the most common.  Then there are Griffawnes, and Crag Spiders.  Another good spot is not to far to the right of the Bridge on a hill.  This is where a lot of reavers spawn.  Very Social, so I'd recommend a group here.  At night time they start spawning undead reavers which are at a higher level.  If you get a good group of mid-level casters (26-34) the druids are great exp and loot as long as you don't mind the faction hit.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
