	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 13th 10:30 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2> I just got feign death recently, and I had looked at a few sites to see if I could find the basics of how to use it, which I did. Well, there is one minor detail that I don't recall seeing anywhere (I might've just overlooked it), that is of the utmost importance. YOU MUST STOP ATTACKING SOMETHING BEFORE FEIGNING DEATH! Maybe everybody else knew that already, hehe, but it never occured to me, but now I know why it failed EVERY TIME. I'm an idiot :)<br> Anyway, after a kindly sage told me about this, I started to try it again and it worked a lot more often.<br> Oh yeah, one more pretty important thing: If you're practicing your feign death in a populated area, don't get up between practices, just stay on the ground and hit the button over and over. Remember that annoying scream? It only happens the first time you fall to the ground. Now the only thing others will hate you for is that "XXX has fallen to the ground" message they have to keep looking at :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Beleni<br>Lowly Monk on Karana</td></tr>
