<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=969434496479></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f969434496479><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=969434496479>RE: wuts the use?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=969434496479#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1490><span id= >Aeglos</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 20th 3:21 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As an Iksar monk, sneak is one of the most useful skills there is.&nbsp;&nbsp;Merchants, while usually never KOS, are almost always dubious to me initially, and you have to be at least apprehensive to sell to them.  It's very difficult to raise faction with a merchant, so I find it much easier to merely sneak up behind 'em and commence with my transactions.  It's also an extremly useful skill for doing quests where your factions not high enough initially to do it.  I'll use Lashun Novashine in North Qeynos as an example.  He'll occasionally walk out into the newbie zone away from guards.  If you give him 2gp or 2 bone chips, he'll give you a nice faction hit with the Qeynos paladins and clerics.  However, since Iksar start out scowling with him, he won't accept the components from you.  I merely used sneak to get indifferent with him to do the quest, then turned in about 50pp in gold to get up to indifferent with him without sneak.  There's many other quests where this skill helps quite a bit. Oh yeah, finally got my Robe of the Lost Circle, 'twas quite a pain at level 27 too if I may say so. Methinks it was worth it though, not as flashy as the Robe of Dalnir, but 'tis quite a nice status symbol, much better than the shackle of rock at least. Ta.<br>&nbsp;<br>glos...<br>Nano-Monk of Neutrality...</td></tr>
