<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96758566520579></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96758566520579><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96758566520579>Stats</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96758566520579#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 29th 5:47 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is a bit of mis-information in this thread.<br><br>Agi has NOTHING to do with how often one blocks/ripostes/dodges/ etc. How often these skills "proc" is based on a random number generated by comparing the lvl and attk rating of the critter the Monk is fighting.&nbsp;&nbsp;This information was revealed by Verant on the official mssg board.  <br><br>Agi affects AC, and how quickly defensive skills advance ONLY.  <br><br>Place ALL of your 20 bonus pts into STR/STA.  Monks have low hp's, and Stam has a direct influence on HP's.  This is especially noticeable at higher lvls, as a mere 10 pts of Stam has a large influence on how many HP's the Monk has.  <br><br>As for Dam avoidance, it's all about AC.  NEVER exchange AC for ANY other stat.  After AC, focus on STR, and then STAM/HP's.  Trying to raise one's AC by raising AGI is not wise, as one only gains 1 AC per 5 AGI, after the AC bonus gained from exeeding 75 AGI.  It is always better to gain AC directly from items.<br><br>For both Ik and Hu Monks. I suggest spending the 20 bonus pts into 10 str and 10 stam.  The other stats are fine where they are.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
