	   <tr><td colspan=2>The funnest place to practice safe fall is in the Academy of Arcane Science in Freeport.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Take the teleporter up to the balcony entrance into the guild.  Rather than going in, run to the ledge and leap off aiming for the teleporter below.  If you hit it right you will land and be teleported back up to the balcony.  Don't stop, run to the edge again, leap again, get teleported up.  <br><br>With a little practice you can be falling almost continiously.  (Well almost, I've gotten 4 in a row now and keep trying for more.)  Makes what could be a dull (rinse/repeat) process to building skill its own kind of fun.<br><br>If you keep your eyes open there are lots of good cliffs or bridges and walkways to practice safe fall.  Just look at them as incidental practice opportunities.  Why run through the city gates when you can leap from the walls?  Why run down the ramps when you can fall?<br><br>Remember to work all those other skills (Mend, Sense Heading, Sneak, Feign Death, Instill) at the same time and you'll be able to keep things maxed out with a minimum of down time.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Beggo</td></tr>
