<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96708913122800></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96708913122800><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96708913122800>Tutorial on which weapons in which hand!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96708913122800#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=950><span id= >Korthil</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Aug 23rd 11:52 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>Allrighty, monkies.&nbsp;&nbsp;As you progress along the Path of Beatdown, you're invariably going to run into the following problem: <br><br>You have 2 1hbs, with 2 different ratios...which do you put in which hand? Does it matter?<br><br>YES.  The EQ damage calcs work in the following way: in your PRIMARY hand, each time you connect with a swing, a constant bonus is added to your weapon's damage.  By our best guess, for 1hb the formula works like this: bonus=(level-25)/3<br>So, this discussion is for all you monkies over 25.  By contrast, the secondary hand gets no bonus at all.  Even with your fists, you'll start noticing that when you double attack but don't dual wield (swing twice with primary hand) you'll do more damage than swinging once with each hand.<br><br>So.  Since the damage bonus is constant, lower delay weapons are better equipped in the primary hand.  This is what made the twig such a ridiculous weapon.  The secondary hand, however, has no bonus at all, so RATIO is all that really matters.  KDs and staves of shielding are a good compliment to your baton or Wu stick.<br><br>When you throw procs into the mix, things get a little muddy. You have to use your best judgement, and take your dex into account, as well as the fact that secondary hand procs are not affected by dex.<br><br>Hope this helps...next post, "2hb Damage Bonus, aka Why the RFS is So Damned Good".<br><br>&nbsp;<br><br>--Korthil</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

