<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96686422430968></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96686422430968><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96686422430968>Skill Point Distribution</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96686422430968#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=634><span id=Scholar>Altizar</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>104 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 9:23 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.11]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Monks are the most skill oriented class around, so the choice of where and how to spend your skill points is a fairly large decision.<br><br>To be honest with you the most skill points you need to spend on any one skill is 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;At level 29, I have all my skills maxed with spending at most 5 points in a single skill.<br><br>These skills you should never put more than 1 point into:<br>1-hb, 2-hb, hand-to-hand, dual wield, double attack, swimming, safe fall, bind wounds, special attacks except flying kick, and Sense Heading(optional but hey if there's nothing else to do while running around the world).<br>These skills are very easy to raise...At the lower levels, don't worry if you level before your weapon skills are maxed, because you will make them up later on as it takes more and more blue creatures to kill to level.<br><br>These skills are harder to raise and you can spend points on them as you see fit:<br>Feign Death, Instill Doubt (better known as Instill Train), Disarm, Flying Kick, Mend.<br><br>You can practice Instill and Feign Death while sitting and resting and still get full healing benefits.<br><br>Mend is by far the toughest raise and keep current with your level.  If you're continously fighting, you will level many times before you're mend skill is maxed, but eventually it will catch-up.<br><br>You can put points into trade skills, however I would not suggest doing this if your wanting a "Cash Cow".  These skill won't start paying dividends until you really get to a level, where you can make just as much money Hunting as you can selling equipment.<br>Think of this, run around Sol A Disarming all the goblins and picking up the FS weapons, FDing as needed and then sell them...That's a good 100-200pp in a very short time :)  Not that I would promoting doing this.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
