<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96676151632324></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96676151632324><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96676151632324>RE: To have weapons or not to wear weapons?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=96676151632324#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=666><span id=Scholar>Zyphyr</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>91 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 20th 4:51 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.91]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here are the damage/delay figures for human monk fists:<br> level range =&gt; damage/delay (ratio)<br><br>1-4 =&gt; 4/36 (.111)<br>5-9 =&gt; 5/36 (.139)<br>10-14 =&gt; 6/36 (.167)<br>15-19 =&gt; 7/36 (.194)<br>20-24 =&gt; 8/36 (.222)<br>25-29 =&gt; 9/35 (.257)<br>30-34 =&gt; 10/34 (.294)<br>35-39 =&gt; 11/33 (.333)<br>40-44 =&gt; 12/32 (.375)<br>45-49 =&gt; 13/31 (.419)<br>50-54 =&gt; 14/30 (.467)<br>55-59 =&gt; 14/28 (.500)<br>60 =&gt; 14/26 (.538)<br><br>At levels 1-24 Iksar monks have the same stats. at 25+ they have the same damage, but delay is 1 higher.<br>( This info is taken from the message boards at <a href="http://thedojo.extropian.org/" target=_new>http://thedojo.extropian.org/</a> )<br><br>For 1HB weapons, if you have a better ratio than the above you should probably use the weapon. If not, you should probably use fists. There is one exception to this - at high levels there is a damage bonus for the weapon in your primary hand. This makes weapons with low delays more valuabe than weapons with high delays at the same ratio, and in some casses better than weapons with better ratios but high delays. For secondary hand, ratio is all that matters.<br><br>For 2HB the issue is a little more murky. The high level damage bonus is higher for a 2H than for a 1H weapon. But, you don't have a second weapon swinging. For the most part you can base your decision on the same factors as a 1HB, but for maximum efficiency you should do some testing to see if the weapon actually performs better/worse than your fists.<br>---<br>Examples :<br>Sap of Piety : 1HB, 13Dam, 33 Delay, wt 2.5. Ratio = .394<br>This weapon has a better ratio than yor fists until 45th. However, its delay become inferior at 40. For primary hand usage it will outdamage your fists until 40th. For secondary hand it is better until 45th.<br><br>Cane of The Tranquil : 1HB, 11Dam, 25 Delay, wt 2.5. Ratio = .440. Better ratio than fists until 50th. Better delay always. For secondary hand it is supperior until you hit 50th. For primary it is definately better to 50, and probably better until 55th. After that point the delays become VERY close. Which is better from 55 through 59 depends on exactly how high the dam bonus is ( I don't have the exact numbers and my monk isn't high enough to test this). At 60, the 1 point improvement in delay shopuld be overshadowed by the significantly higher damage (but it may not, I am not 100% positive).<br><br>Cracked Staff : 1HB, Damage 5, delay 32, wt 8.5. Ratio = .156. Better ratio until 10th. Better Delay until 39. Good for off hand until you hit 10th level. Only good for primary until then as well, as the damage bonus doesn't kick in until around the time your hands catch up to the staffs delay. With no damage bons, only delay matters.<br><br>Modulating Rod : 1HB, Damage 8, Delay 26, wt 1.0. Ratio = .308. Better ratio till you hit 35th. Better delay until 60th. Major drawback - you need to get a 44+ mage to summon one for you whenever you log in. Good for both primary and secondary until 35th, for the same reasons as the cracked staff.<br>---<br><br>These are just some of the possible 1HBs. Additionaly, you need to consider the extra weight of the weapons and the effects that will have on your AC. At low levels it is essentially irrelevant, but as you move up it becomes a major issue.<br><br>I haven't done enough testing/work with 2HB to give good examples on those, so I will refrain from attempting to do so beyond.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Zyphyr Runnersbane<br>60th Vending Machine<br>Cult of the Ancient Wyrm<br>Solusek Ro<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
