<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=966653877403></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f966653877403><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=966653877403>RE: Soloing Guide for 20+</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=966653877403#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 10:57 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I noticed that these are mostly for human monks.. Here is what I found (Being an iksar)<br><br>Level 1-3: I found in The Swamp of No hope. And, except for frogloks, the mobs aren't social. I fought just off to the right of the path barely past the building. If you DO get in trouble, the guards are right there. Now, you could do the curscale quests at levels 1-3, that would work too. Some good armor at low levels, but not sure of the weight. Even if the weight is high, being a pound or 2 overweight will only decrease your AC by 1 or 2 at such a low level.<br><br>From levels 3-10 really, I stuck in 'the pit' in the Field of Bone. I stayed on the right side (mountain side) until around 8 when I switched to the ocean side. Just remember to pull near the wall. If you don't, you may find yourself fighting a few more mobs than you expected. <br><br>NOTE: Not sure if this bug has been fixed yet or not, but if a mob starts running away into the wall, you might as well zone then. I only remember this being with the spiders, but it could be with other mobs as well. Anyway, the mob will run into the wall, disappear, then start hitting you. I could never find the mob in the zone, but it was a phantom, hitting me. The guards didn't take care of it, so just zone.<br><br>10-15: I was in the The tower (Kurn's I think..?) Fighting skeletons. There's a great hidden room there you can pull to, or the entrance. To get to the hidden room, turn right when you enter the main room, and follow the wall. It will turn 90 degrees, go past a door near the corner, then you will progress farther down. Keep walking straight and you'll run right through the wall. <br>If you wanted to, you could easily play in the pit on the left side some more if skeletons aren't appealing. But, with the 400+ bone chips I got, I sold them for 2-4 pp a stack in the lake of ill omen. Took a while, but financed my Cured Silk =)<br><br>At 15, I tentatively ventured into The overthere (It's past warsliks). I fought some weak cats and such, and eventually worked my way all the way up to 23, where I am currently in SolA. <br>Give me a shout if you see me =)<br><br>Arden, 24, Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
